<Author>ua1953
<Content>Pleasant Berlin Hotel After reviewing a number of hotels in Berlin on-line we chose the Best Western Euro-Hotel and booked directly with a call to Best Western. The price was a bargain and suprisingly included breakfast. Check-in was easy and the desk staff was pleasant with good English skills. The room was typical for Germany, fairly small , but well furnished and very clean. The only problem we encountered was the radiator in the room didn't heat as well as expected. The one in the bath was fine. The full buffet breakfast was very good and had a great deal of variety. The hotel is located in the former Eastern area of Berlin and there were a nuimber of Turkish stores around the hotel. We chose restaurants from a sheet provided by the desk clerk which we could walk to and were not disappointed. A major Karstad store was very close and the U bahn stop was just out side the door along with a taxi stand. 
