<Author>CheshireCouple
<Content>Wouldn't hesitate to recommend it We stayed in this hotel for two nights in September 2007 and found it spotlessly clean, quite luxurious for the price, fairly modern and very comfortable indeed. We only had brief dealings with the receptionist but she was friendly and helpful. It was easy to travel to this hotel from Schonefeld airport thanks to the 171 bus which cost 鈧?.10 each and ran straight from the airport to virtually outside the door of the hotel, although it is a long ride and takes about an hour. Buy your bus ticket from the machine outside the airport doors (and from the Hermannplatz station on the way back) and validate it by getting it punched in the machine on board the bus.This hotel is also ideally situated for the U-Bahn underground system, with Hermannplatz station right outside providing easy access to the whole city, with trains every few minutes.The breakfast was great with high quality food and drink, although we did catch the staff clearing away the buffet 10 minutes before it was supposed to end, which I think is unacceptable as there were still people walking in for breakfast, including us.There are plenty of kebab/pizza/noodle take-aways (and a McDonalds) right outside the hotel which offer food at twice the quality and half the price of equivalent places in Britain, and stay open till late. If you're happy to get by on take-away food in your hotel room, you can exist by spending next to nothing.There is a small shop a few doors away from the hotel, open until 2.00am and selling wine, beer, confectionery etc very cheaply - 500ml bottles of strong German lager straight from the fridge for 鈧?.55 each!Overall this hotel is a good base if you want to explore Berlin for a couple of days, and I doubt you could find anything better for the price. 
