<Author>JJudy
<Content>Interesting location, hot room I stayed here myself in June 2007 on a two day trip to Berlin.Hotel was clean, price was reasonable, location near Turkish area of Berlin interesting, with excellent shwarma near by, some of the best I ever tasted, at great prices. Although it is close to the subway (across the street), it is quite a distance by subway from the centre of the western part of the city (the Ku'Damm) although not too far from the Alexanderplatz in the eastern part. The hotel is not located in a touristy area. Staff was efficient, if not overly friendly.My one complaint is that I could not figure out the air conditioning in the room, and the room was hot, stuffy and smelly for lack of ventilation. Iam not sure that the hotel had air conditioning or internal ventilation at all. Then again, I could have asked for assistance, but did not. My room was a single and quite small.Decent breakfast served as part of the price, although when in Europe I prefer a quick espresso on the street rather than a sit down breakfast. A good place to stay on a budget. Not much in terms of facilities such as a gym, pool, etc, but the hotel does advertise that it is affiliated with a health club near by.Good neighborhood bar a few doors down, lots of locals hang out. Friendly clientele. Drink of preference definitely mixed drinks or beer, not white wine. 
