<Content>Another good review! I can't really understand how people can moan about this hotel!It is on a direct bus oute from Schonfeld,which is ideal when you arrive late at night.Bus 171 will get you to the hotel in about 45mins to an hour,all for 2.10 Euro's each!The Hotel is based in a predominantly Turkish area,and has very easy access to Hermanplatz U bahn.There are ecent eating places nearby(especially if you like Pizza,you can get decent ones for 3 euros!!!) there is even a subway and Mac Donalds if you are abit sad!!!The Hotel room was big BUT it faces a busy road which can have noise implications.If you have kids you may want a back room.When we were there it was HOT! There is no AC but we got fan and there's a mini bar with a good fridge.A shop nearby allows you to buy your own drinks and use the fridge!!!Breakfast was buffet style and was more than adequate and comprised of the usual Euro delights of breads,cheeses,meats,fruit,cereals,coffee and a nice touch of Earl Grey tea!!!Overall this may be a problem if you have kids and are facing the busy road,although the double glazing drowns out the noise,if its hot at night you wouldn't want the windows open and a fan might keep you awake.The location is ideal for travelling around and it is relativelt inexpensive.The staff were always friendly and helpful. 
