<Author>zenobie
<Content>Euro Hotel is comfortable  I liked this hotel. It was comfortable, pleasant, convenient, and seemed to be meticululously well-run. I was travelling alone, and was given a single room of a reasonable size for one - not just a converted cupboard. The bed was comfortable and the shower/toilet was clean  attractive.I chose the hotel mainly because of its location : in Hermannplatz right at the terminus of the airport bus (No. 171) from Schonefeld Airport. That's very convenient - esp. when you arrive at around midnight, and are a bit wary of being ripped-off by taxis taking you across a huge  strange city. The city U-Bahn is literally just around the corner, and it took me straight to Alexanderplatz in c. 12 minutes. The bus stop (for other buses places in town e.g. Charlottenburg) is at the hotel front door. People in Berlin asked me: Why are you staying all the way down there? That's not where tourists go. But I always said the location suited me fine. I never needed a taxi once: I always knew where I was going.The quality of the hotel was a pleasant surprise: the cold breakfast buffet was large, varied and very saitsfying - although the only hot dish was scrambled eggs ( but that's minor).It was lovely to eat breakfast on the top storey while looking out over the panorama of Berlin.I took my own electric kettle, coffee  milk powder with me, as the hotel didn't supply these for evening coffee in the bedroom.But they had complimentary coffee on offer in the foyer: you helped yourself as you wanted. I was even allowed free coffee after I had checked out and was waiting for the airport bus. Little things can mean a lot. I asked for 2 pillows instead of one, and got them. I was asked to pay a 50 Euro deposit for the mini-bar when I arrived. I said I wouldn't, because I had no intention of using it (I suspected having been ripped-off in other hotels) and I asked for it to be emptied straightaway. At midnight, the young receptionist didn't think he was allowed to do that: but the following evening when I returned, the minibar was empty and stayed empty all week. I liked that - getting what you ask for.I enjoyed my stay: the staff were pleasant  very helpful. 
