<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Great location for Schoenefeld Just returned from four days in Berlin, staying at the Best Western Euro. My friends and I had one triple room (with one double  one single bed) and one single room between us. Both rooms were very clean (cleaned and towels changed every day) and the beds were very comfortable. We were on the sixth floor which helped reduce traffic noise, as the hotel's at a corner next to a crossroads with traffic lights. There's a phone, a minibar, TV and internet access. The restaurant on the top floor served an excellent breakfast every morning - it's a self service buffet with a large selection of breads, meat, cheese, eggs, yoghurts and drinks.The best thing about the hotel was the location. If you're coming from Schoenefeld you can get the 171 Airport bus to Hermannplatz (the last stop) for 2 Euros. It takes about an hour but it's also a regular bus service. There are a lot of people getting on and off - not the best if you have large suitcases. You could take the U-Bahn from Rudow station instead - It's about five mins from the airport in a taxi but there is also a station outside the airport. The hotel is right next to the Hermannplatz U-Bahn station. Buy a day ticket for 6 Euros (or a group ticket for up to five people for EUR15) and take advantage of Berlin's integrated subway system, you'll only have to wait 10 minutes at the most for a train. We had no problems getting around. The streets around the hotel are fine, we didn't feel unsafe at any time. There's a great Croatian restaurant about 2 minutes walk down the street and there's also a Lebanese one nearby. You're also close to a bakery, shops, bars and a McDonalds (if you really have to!).I would definately recommend the hotel. It was between this and the Abacus Tierpark when I was deciding but this hotel is better located for getting into the centre of Berlin. 
